INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jej3700','letter','1780-07-18','Philadelphia','PA','US','Joseph','Jones','','George','Washington','','individual','','A report from the Board of War, in consequence of a letter of General Gates\'s to Congress, referred to the Board, respecting the promotion of Colonel Daniel Morgan to the office of Brigadier-General, now lies upon the table','ltr_jej3700.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jej3701','letter','1780-08-07','Philadelphia','PA','US','Joseph','Jones','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have my hopes we shall yet be able to do somefhing important upon the arrival of the French reenforcement, as I presume their fleet will then command the water, without which, I confess, I have no sanguine expectations.','ltr_jej3701.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jej3702','letter','1780-09-06','Philadelphia','PA','US','Joseph','Jones','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have received jour favor of The 10th ultimo, upon the subject of a report respecting a certain gentleman, and thank you for the freedom and candid manner of your communications.','ltr_jej3702.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jej3703','letter','1780-10-02','','VA','US','Joseph','Jones','','George','Washington','','individual','','Congress having taken some steps towards completing the Federal Union, which I anxiously wish to accomplish, induced me to be here early in the session','ltr_jej3703.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jej3704','letter','1781-02-21','Philadelphia','PA','US','Joseph','Jones','','George','Washington','','individual','','I beg leave to mention to you a young gentleman, captured by the enemy when the Buckskin fell into their hands in the Chesapeake Bay, and who was put on shore under parole, and wishes to be discharged','ltr_jej3704.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jej3705','letter','1781-05-16','Philadelphia','PA','US','Joseph','Jones','','George','Washington','','individual','','The late movements of Cornwallis and Phillips indicate a junction of their armies on the Roanoke, from whence they may direct their operations north or south, as they shall see best, without the fear','ltr_jej3705.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_jej3706','letter','1783-02-27','Philadelphia','PA','US','Joseph','Jones','','George','Washington','','individual','','Congress have been, for some time past, almost wholly employed in devising some general and adequate funds for paying the interest, and in time sinking the principal, of the public debt','ltr_jej3706.txt','hans@broughdesign.com',NULL,Now(),NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853');
